Diet for children suffering from obesity: No breakfast and sausage for dinner
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 weigh more than normal; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% suffer from obesity.
According to the latest study, children suffering from obesity usually come from families leading an unhealthy lifestyle.
We again see the importance of the environment and patterns of behavior that accompany a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausages appear on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children with normal weight.
More than 19% of children suffering from obesity ate fries for dinner on the eve of a survey related to an educational event called Obesity is no coincidence.
Moreover, families of children suffering from obesity do not engage in sports. This, however, applies to most families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said that their parents find time to exercise at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of last academic year, involving almost 900 primary school students across Bohemia.
The event Obesity - it is not an accident was held for the second year in a row, with the support of insurance company V<0xC5><0xA1>eobecn<0xC3><0xA1> zdravotn<0xC3><0xAD> poji<0xC5><0xA1>t'ovna and company Unilever.
To date, more than 12,000 schoolchildren from grades 4 to 8 have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and sufficient exercise are the main determinants of the rapidly growing number of children who are either overweight or obese.
“For example, only half of the respondents said they eat five times a day, according to the breakfast-recommended-lunch-recommended-lunch-dinner scheme, and this is one of the essential conditions for proper nutrition,” says one of the study’s findings.
No lunch and no sausage in the evenings.
Experts warn that even relative details such as the constant time of a family breakfast are important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families have breakfast together.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast separately.
The worst finding is that in every tenth family, people don’t eat breakfast at all.
And yet breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The study found that fried foods were more commonly consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sweet soft drinks every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children play sports regularly, this figure is more than doubled – to 15% – when it comes to their parents.
Make your own menu.
In another part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the products offered and based on their tastes and preferences.
“The food preferences of Czech children aged 12-15 years are far from ideal when it comes to healthy eating.”
Their favorite food includes a large number of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
“A particular concern is the high popularity of sweet soft drinks,” the study concludes.
As the main dinner dish, the pasta beat the bird with a small overhang.
However, the children showed almost no interest in bean, fish and vegetable dishes.
Striving for a healthy lifestyle
The study also showed that children are willing to change their eating habits provided they are provided with relevant information.
“Many participants in the study’s control group demonstrated a significant shift in preferences toward healthy eating when they filled out a questionnaire after completing a lecture Obesity is not an accident,” the project said.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sweet soft drinks - more children began to prefer them just water.
In addition, as the main dish, children were more likely to celebrate poultry and fish, limiting the number of sweet dishes and pastries.
A stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article about trainings for stylists, I visited the volume of information at introductory classes.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures by three experts in this field; tips on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a seminar on how all this works in real life.
Further, more.
The closer we are to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
The training is held every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, (there are no men on the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
One has a short neck, the other has a male figure without proper forms, another weighs more than the norm.
The stylist should know how to visually reduce wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or add missing volumes.
We were given advice on how to emphasize the figure of women such as Jennifer Lopez, i.e., owners of a more lush chest and thighs and a narrow waist, and not to dress them too provocatively.
For example, if the difference in the size of the waist and hips is so large that you can not pick up a skirt or pants, you should have at least one thing sewn to order.
You will obviously not regret the funds invested, because perfectly sitting clothes are priceless.
In a skirt sewn to order, you will feel much better than in the one that constantly goes off, rolls, undresses the waist, etc.
Owners of boys' figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with ruffles, application, embroidery or folds.
Given the abundance of such information and types of figures, I’m glad I have a whole week to realize it all.
And yet, I'm afraid, it's too much, given the homework we got.
Each participant of the courses had to come up with two outfits for any celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We must take into account their modern appearance, their style in clothes and the type of figure.
I'm going to dress Miranda Kerr, who you might know from Victoria's Secret ad campaigns.
I’m happy for myself because it’s so much easier to wear than, say, Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who recently made a ton of improvements (please keep in mind that I’m exaggerating), or a very young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut clothes out of magazines or find them online, print and process them using graphic programs.
Mudboard - so called the result of work - then reflects our own style and attitude to the graphic image.
It is important to keep in mind the graphic component of the style.
The stylist does not just dress real people, but creates product pages in magazines (based on special instructions, such as fashion bags, coats, etc.).
This is what the stylist and designer Mario Kamenik told us.
But it was only on Sunday.
The stylist needs a general knowledge
The Saturday lecture, full of information about the types of figures, was brought to life by three guests - specialists in this field.
Stylist, Honza Pokorny; fashion designer, Jacob Polanka; and fashion photographer Ben Ranch.
Jacob reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should use this fact.
A good stylist can use one item of clothing in different ways.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a trench coat can be worn in the usual way, on top of jeans and T-shirts, like a coat; but it can also be worn on a naked body, without cuffs, like a dress.
Another option is to roll up the sleeves or lift the collar, and the whole image completely changes.
“Play with him,” he said.
Anyway, I most appreciated the following advice: "For your work you should know the rules perfectly."
Then you can start breaking them," Jacob told us.
Here I have finally understood why we are brushing up on all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see quite different.
Not to mention fashion shows.
From Ben, the photographer, I learned that the stylist should have more outfit options on hand than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a fashion review on ten pages (equivalent to ten outfits) I have to be ready to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that in the picture, the subject of clothing often looks and works in combination with others, not at all like in reality.
We must keep this in mind when creating an image.
Honza Pokorny confirmed that often image and style is half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who doesn’t have a stunning vocal, but her image and marketing have made her a world star.
The attitude to the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even famous people often consider this superfluous (and believe that it is enough to be a specialist in something, and the way they look - secondary).
And if someone finally lets us create their style, we should expect them to call us a different (less) size than the one they really wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids wrote anything about what some celebrity was up to / losing weight, etc.
On Sunday, Gonza and Mario emphasized that it is not enough for the stylist to understand fashion and be able to pick up the outfit.
Our job is mainly to communicate with the people we dress; that’s why it’s important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to appreciate people, not to indulge them and to stick to their opinion.
“If the manager asks you to look at her clothes and add a few beautiful things, you can’t throw away her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are terrible.”
“Find at least a few things you can praise, and advise what you can wear with them,” says Mario.
He also showed us what a working bag should specifically fit.
This is a bag that you tie around your waist to carry everything you need.
In addition to obvious things, such as scissors, sticky roller or English pins, it should be a nylon thread (stylists use it when shooting some items, for example, a bag or hat), special clips to fasten the fabric on the back in case the clothes are too big for them (shoes are too big for them)
To distract from the lectures and get some practical experience, we learned how to make the correct lining on the soles of the shoes.
Even when shooting in a studio where the floor is smooth, the soles can get damaged — not to mention shooting on the street.
And here we go with the sticker.
You should not touch the shoes with scissors so as not to spoil them.
This requires real skill.
I was glad that Mario praised my work.
I didn’t like these skills.
This is only part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend courses.
I’m starting to realize that being a professional stylist isn’t as easy as anyone might say.
V Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Overview
What was supposed to be a carefree walk turned into a routine morning commute to work because of a series of completely inappropriate and careless mistakes.
Ambitions have been met to some extent, but it doesn’t matter, as no one clearly wanted to do extra work.
Before the release of the new version with the subtitle "Escape" had high hopes.
It was expected to move the previous series of Need For Speed in a new direction; demonstration versions indicated that the game would take a worthy place in the racing game genre.
We were curious to see parts of the game where the main character gets out of the car and runs away.
As is often the case with NFS, in the end, much is different from what we expected.
The game is a pretty good arcade race, but the overall impression spoils a few unnecessary mistakes that have been present in this series of games for several years.
And so, in reality, these are not mistakes, but the manifestation of the inexplicable laziness of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You become part of a story whose protagonist, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You get in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to be the first to get to New York.
This idea has some interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race goes on its route, separate stages are held in a diverse and interesting environment.
Therefore, there is no feeling that the same thing happens all the time in the game.
Despite the fact that the schedule is at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some tracks are nice to look at.
But the game doesn’t have strong emotions.
Although driving through the desert, in the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the race from time to time brings to life an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert you get into a sandstorm, significantly reducing visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to fall under the avalanche.
The individual races are pretty well organized.
There are only a few varieties, but that’s enough.
For a while you try to overtake several rivals (essentially a regular race); then you try to improve the time (standard race with a stopwatch); or you compete with one opponent.
Among other things, you come across the police from time to time, which makes your task even more complicated.
The components on the outside of the car are new.
It’s just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
Although it is surprising that these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (just three to be exact).
In fact, it turns out that it’s good for the game because this property doesn’t get bored; given all of the above, it’s one of the things that makes the game more entertaining.
The racing model follows in the footsteps of previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you’re looking for a real-life imitation, you’ll have to look elsewhere.
And yet this driving model is very suitable for dynamic racing, although you can find better options on the market.
So far so good.
However, after a while, problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
From such a game you do not expect complex transformations and collisions, but if you have no idea before a collision with an object, how your car will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, overtaking or passing machines in a dense flow, you sometimes slightly touch another machine. And yet sometimes in a practically similar situation your machine begins to spin furiously.
Or the shards broke.
This is not so important thanks to the restart system, but it is enough to spoil the fun.
Reboots are arranged so that if you break or go far away from the track, the game takes you back to the point where it broke.
However, only five restarts are available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful in case something doesn’t work out, but you can’t fully rely on it.
Sometimes restarts are not enough, and you have to learn a separate section of the race on your own.
An important disadvantage of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to go a certain way, otherwise you just won’t fit in.
In other cases, you meet civilian cars in a specific location in the same configuration regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier, or a minute later.
This is especially irritating in situations where you see your opponent easily passing between two cars moving in the opposite direction, whereas when you get there, the cars are already positioned so that you either need to move them around or slow down.
It doesn’t matter when you’re around them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens right in front of your nose.
Competitors have other advantages.
During the game, you find several places where, regardless of the time, the same opponent overtakes you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on the long bridge where you go in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent has to stand in front of you no matter what.
The fact is that when he drives in front of you, he makes you look worse, which leads to one or more accidents on this site.
You can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and full of adrenaline, but it is so obvious that it quickly begins to cause irritation.
Too bad, because despite the simple driving model, the game is entertaining and sometimes so full of events that you do not have time to pay attention to what is happening around you.
It doesn’t matter what makes you miss out – a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during a race is unusual.
You need to keep track of the gas stations along the way, as it is on them your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
The machines are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars are for straight sections of the highway; and exotic super-sports cars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain tracks.
The main mode of the story mode is closely related to the challenge mode; it is a race on individual sections that you will learn over the course of the game.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and points, common for challenges and story modes.
Many opportunities are available to achieve a higher level of driving: from cars to profile data.
In addition, the profile is associated with the online function Autolog, which, among other things, compares the results achieved by you with the results of other players, and provides communication with the public.
Here is another drawback that is difficult to understand; it is an example from the last race in a sequence.
You and your car get into the subway tunnel (we'll assume that's the case) where you race on the tracks in the dark (we'll assume that's the case).
Your speedometer shows the numbers from 150 to 200 km/h (we’ll assume so) when a subway train suddenly hits you from behind, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
Over the course of a few days, our editors discussed whether no one really thought for a second at the time of creating the game, or whether its creators really consider us such fools.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video series is for the most part pleasant, sometimes even stunning.
Although it is a pity that in some critical moments the quality of the recording, sometimes quite strongly, decreases.
This is especially true for events with a large number of participants, where a good record would not help you much either.
Sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the amateur.
To please as wide a youth audience as possible, the soundtrack 'entered compositions of different styles'; but hardly many people will buy the game because of its music.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: Escape is quite messy.
If the game were to avoid obvious unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that Escape is the best part of the NFS in the last few years.
In any case, the game leaves a feeling of incompleteness.
Sure, it’s good fun, but be prepared for the drawbacks that will blind you as an airport projector.
