He knew the original design and knew the tasks that stood in front of the building, a building that had already lost some of its grandeur and lightness when it was moved to Vienna and converted.
The problems that arose during the last reconstruction were much more serious. The building was an "energy absorber", says Krishanitz.
The window profiles on the glass facade were replaced, a fiberglass reinforced safety glass was inserted, and the glass roof was replaced with a high-strength safety glass.
The steel overhangs of the thermal bridge were reinforced or replaced, and asbestos was removed from the ceilings.
