A park or a forest?
The architects agree with the possibility of a competition after disputes about contributions
The municipal competition for 16 doors has resumed the debate about the role of Colserola in Barcelona
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the now-defunct Barcelona Capital Corporation (BCC), this administration printed promotional leaflets for Kolserola.
The booklet described the mountain as a large park of the capital of Barcelona.
Moreover, it was accompanied by a comparison in the pictures with the Central Park of New York.
With the death of SCB in 1987, the park again took place in the minds of many as the highest point of Barcelona as the capital of Catalonia, one of the few that are oriented not north-south, but up (up)-down (sea).
The positioning of Kolserola as a natural park contradicts this idea.
The prototype was not the Central Park, but Yellowstone, with a wild boar as the bear Yogi.
This was the case until, in September, the council announced huge competitions consisting of 16 competitions for many other gates in Kolserol.
By the gate is meant the idea of the park, no doubt.
Either that, or someone wants to put the gate on the field.
The question is: Colserola? Park or mountain?
Competitions, and their organizational side, and their influence on the city, are a topic for discussion by all architects of Barcelona.
This is hardly the most recurring topic discussed when two members of this clan of chosen people get to know each other in an elevator.
And this fact leads to one of the few coincidences between what the three architects of Barcelona say and the scientists who were present.
Miguel Roldan, Daniel Modolo and Mara Bayona: the competition is appropriate
For Roldan, once the coastline is reached, it becomes “necessary” to discuss the “front side of the mountain” when Ildefon Serra’s proposal, a mountain with green apples, has not been implemented.
“We have to admit that Barcelona’s biggest park is the beach.
Among other things, thanks to its excellent accessibility.
The Colserola is more complex,” says the architect, for whom the title “Colserola gate” contains a “word trap”: we should not think of them “as an entrance to the park, but as a limitation of some areas where we should act.”
Modolo, like Roldan and Bayon with experience in urban construction, called the proposal an “intellectual task” with “some dangers.”
Risks arising from the "uncertainty of forecasting public space" after the experience of the 80s, which ended on the Forum site "his swan song".
The first fear is actually limiting the boundaries where you can build.
“The limitation of something is the preparation of the next step,” that is, the transition.
“We need to think about new urban planning tools because current [as far as the General Capital Plan (GGP) is concerned] can lead to real trouble.”
Closer to the case, Modolo believes that the simplification of the Kolserola valley "can be understood as a park, Barcelona, and not" as a purely topographical issue.
Modolo recalls that there is already work done outside of Calcerola, which “do not miss the ears”, although he is grateful for the opportunity offered by the city to his profession, to join this project “from the beginning”.
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain to the city is a pass that allows architects to enter into the debate, but “he doubts” whether this technical profile is what should lead interdisciplinary teams (“success,” he claims), which should have created: “Architects should only be an instrument.”
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that asks the name of this part is complex, since the rules of the competition lack a common type of Colserola: "There were announced 16 intersecting competitions, - he says - in the sense of sea-mountains, but there is no longitudinal reading to see and understand the area of the goal".
This makes it necessary, at least in his case, to decide to participate in 16 competitions.
On the other hand, a project for a single gate can intersect by program and definition with an architect’s project for a neighboring gate.
From your point of view, the advice should be to ensure that the strip directly above Ronda de Dalt should provide in its entirety an area equipped to create a smooth transition between the city and the green.
