By 2017, the structural deficit of the state budget should be reduced by 0.75% of gross domestic product (GDP) each year, and since 2017, the structural deficit of the state budget of the federal state in any year should not exceed 0.35% of GDP, and the land, like the municipalities, should represent balanced budgets.
